Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.52, 5, 53, 2 or 121, 3). Name Aphrodisios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1228)
